="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Consider some alarming facts about credit reporting:</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><font color="#222222"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff"><font color="#343434">79% of all credit reports contain errors&nbsp;</font><font color="#2f7bb0">[1]</font></span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><font color="#222222"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff"><font color="#343434">29% of credit reports contained errors so damaging that it could instantly result in the denial of credit&nbsp;</font><font color="#2f7bb0">[2]</font></span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1.27cm; margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Don&rsquo;t let misinformation on your credit file affect your business. Business members receive credit file management service to ensure highly accurate files, protection from fraud and empowerment to protect themselves from disputed credit amounts.</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">[1] Consumer reports and public interest research group</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 2; orphans: 2">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">[2]http://www.consumerfed.org/pdfs/121702CFA_NCRA_Credit_Score_Report_Final.pdf</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n', NULL),
(3, 'consumers', 'consumers', 'Credit Seekers', 'A Problematic Industry', '<p>\r\n	Credit reporting issues are everywhere in North America. Identity theft alone resulted in $50 billion in losses to consumers and financial institutions in 2007.<a href="#ftn1">[1]</a> &nbsp;Forty nine million people in North America have been a victim of identity theft<a href="#ftn2">[2]</a> &nbsp;at least twice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The facts about credit reporting are alarming:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		79% of all credit reports contain errors, <a href="#ftn3">[3]</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		29% of credit reports contained errors so damaging, that it would instantly result in the denial of credit. <a href="#ftn4">[4]</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		fixing&nbsp;inaccuracies on ones credit report, typically costs consumers an average of $12,000 and takes up to two years to correct if it ever get corrected. <a href="#ftn5">[5]</a></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Consumers spend $3.6 billion per year on credit monitoring services that&nbsp;delivery little results&nbsp;.<a href="#ftn6">[6]</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The animosity and frustration of consumers toward the three existing credit reporting agencies are well documented and continue to grow due to lack of direct response to the consumer. &nbsp;<a href="#ftn7">[7]</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Despite repeated attempts by the&nbsp;governing bodies&nbsp;ordering them to offer service to the consumer, no lasting change occurs. This is due to the fact that their business is not based on customer satisfaction and empowerment but on a simple profit structure through mass data-mining. Court fines are simply considered as the cost of doing business for companies with this type of business model.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Through unique consumer-centric processes, products and services as well as the exceptional and practical value it provides to its members, <strong>EnCharge intends to&nbsp;compete against&nbsp;the credit reporting industry, by offering a&nbsp;new&nbsp;choice called&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;Consumer Risk Management &amp; Reporting&quot; </strong>defining a new industry;&nbsp;servicing consumers and creditors&nbsp;both in a meaningful way. <u><strong>Join today, Be EnCharge</strong></u></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn1"></a>[1] Federal Trade Commission, House Report on Identity Theft</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn2"></a>[2] Federal Trade Commission, House Report on Identity Theft, 2008</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn3"></a>[3] Consumer reports and public interest research group</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn4"></a>[4] http://www.consumerfed.org/pdfs/121702CFA_NCRA_Credit_Score_Report_Final.pdf</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn5"></a>[5] Consumer Reports.org, April 2007, &ldquo;Costly Credit Monitoring Services Offer Limited Fraud Protection&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn6"></a>[6] Consumer Reports.org, April 2007, &ldquo;Costly Credit Monitoring Services Offer Limited Fraud Protection&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a name="ftn7"></a>[7]FTC, House Report Credit Industry, 2008; PIRG, NACA,Consumer Reports.org</p>\r\n', NULL),
(4, 'fraudbuster-c', 'consumers/fraudbuster-c', 'Fraud Protection', 'Identity Theft and Fraud Protection', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.48cm; widows: 2; orphans: 2">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#222222"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff"><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Due to the explosion of informa</span>tion, it has also become easier for an individual&rsquo;s personal information to be obtained and used illegally.&nbsp; This crime, known as Identity Theft, has become an ever increasing problem.&nbsp;&nbsp;<font color="#343434">Security is of paramount importance at EnCharge. Social security and identification numbers (SSN and SIN) will never be used for account identification, verification, or any other purpose.</font></span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Unlike our competitors, EnCharge member&rsquo;s financial information is protected by voice print biometrics verification system. By using voice-print biometrics technology at each point of entry, data collection is automated while accessing individual files and reporting is biometrically encoded. As a result, registered members, lending institutions and reporting companies are armed with the ability to access files solely via the voice portal &ndash; the ultimate way to protect information.</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">One of the many advantages of our biometric system is that multiple accounts cannot be created for any single member. Individual voice prints are linked to a unique file; each voice print has the power to authorize any release of credit file information. Therefore, members can be assured that no fraud will occur on their EnCharge file.</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">The biometric security also blocks fraudulent activity since fraudsters are unable to reproduce the voice print. The voice print analytic software detects reproductions so a recording of a member&rsquo;s voice would not be able to unlock another member&rsquo;s account. There is no incentive for anyone to attempt to create an EnCharge credit file in another person&rsquo;s name since a new credit file only contains information derived from a unique voice print, which is biometrically paired with the member for life. Duplicate voice print pairing is only permitted in rare cases (for example, for a power of attorney or parent/guardian account) and only where complete documentation is filed and verified.</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Persons attempting fraud who fail to provide irrefutable proof of intent may be added to a list of known fraudsters, or KFL (Known Fraudster List). Within the EnCharge environment, those on the KFL might be subject to:</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Prevention of account creation</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Reduced likelihood of obtaining credit</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Higher interest rates from creditors</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">Potential prosecution</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="background: #ffffff">All new member applications are biometrically processed against the KFL before the account is finally approved.</span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><font color="#343434"><span style="font-style: normal"><span style="font-weight: normal"><span style="background: #ffffff">Since EnCharge credit files are constructed with verified factual information, they build value over time and reveal trends that allow members to be partially insulated from negative circumstances. Meanwhile, creditors are provided with a more comprehensive picture of character as it relates to risk.</span></span></span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n', 3),
(5, 'creditors', 'creditors', 'Creditors', 'Overview', '<p>\r\n	Welcome to EnCharge, the next generation in credit reporting. We are a unique full-service credit reporting management company offering unprecedented financial and risk management services to banks, creditors,&nbsp;business and consumers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We ensure 100%&nbsp;error free&nbsp;credit reports, shield creditors and business from fraudsters, and provide the most advanced risk report and score available.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Credit/financial institution members will be provided&nbsp; <strong>free</strong> access to the credit reports of all our members.&nbsp;We offer a more precise and decisive risk score based upon enCharge&#39;s proprietary risk algorithms and processes.&nbsp;In addition, &nbsp;we have only one credit file per member and real time identity verification processes that protect you from fraudsters.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Benefits to member credit financial institutions include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		No fee membership enrollment.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		No access fee for members reports</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Biometric verification stopping fraud related transactions before they happen.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ease of implementation and functionality with on-going support.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Accurate and meaningful credit scores.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		100% accurate credit reports.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Indicative and predictive risk assessment tools.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Streamlined process for filing credit reports, reducing operational costs.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Easy enrollment and user friendly web-based applications.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Toll free access to live agents.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Marketing opportunities and a competitive lateral and horizontal growth opportunity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Member creditor benefits are free for all creditors after a no-cost enrollment.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>sign up now&nbsp;by clicking on the Join Now tab on the left</strong></p>\r\n', NULL);
