(15, 'control', 'consumers/control', 'Get Power and Control', 'Your credit file', '<p>\r\n	<img align="right" alt="Control" height="111" src="/images/icons/control.jpg" width="171" /><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18px; ">EnCharge offers the power of identity security, accurate lender information, verified files, and complete account access. We keep the process simple by not only providing members with control over file access, but also allowing unlimited file-content browsing and an efficient resolution service managed by expert agents in near real time. Members can call with questions for our team to research and answer by using the fastest technologies available.&nbsp;Give us a call, email us, or make online comments at your convenience. Members are a key part of the accuracy and protection process. We want them fully involved in credit report management.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; widows: 2; orphans: 2">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; widows: 2; orphans: 2">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">You are EnCharge!</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n', 3),
(16, 'thescore', 'consumers/thescore', 'The Score', 'Your Credit Rating and Score', '<p>\r\n	<img align="right" alt="Credit Report" height="111" src="/images/icons/credit-report.jpg" width="171" /><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18px; ">The EnCharge scoring paradigm is the most advanced in the credit risk management marketplace. It is designed to measure true risk by going beyond the traditional debt-to-income ratio and credit history analysis.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">EnCharge&rsquo;s unique algorithm generates two scores designed to give creditors better tools to measure risk. The first score, measuring 300 to 900, highlights bill payment history and patterns. The second score, also measuring 300 to 900, shows a more complete picture by including factors such as assets, liens, and bankruptcies.&nbsp;</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#222222"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><font color="#343434">Due to policies regulating the process of score reviewing, some banks will not be able to use EnCharge&rsquo;s score as the ultimate deciding factor in approving a credit-seeker&#39;s request for credit for two years. However, banks&nbsp;</font><font color="#343434"><u>are&nbsp;</u></font><font color="#343434">authorized to use our services to ensure accuracy and confirm identity while our members continue building their EnCharge credit history.</font></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Traditional credit reporting can spoil a person&rsquo;s good rating when courts get involved. EnCharge believes you have the legal right to contest a bill in court without bringing down your credit. EnCharge has access to specially trained experts who review court documents to determine if a judgement should be included as a risk in your file.</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">As an EnCharge member, you will know what your credit score is and what it means in real terms. Your statistics will be compared to industry benchmarks so you can measure your score against societal norms. And, you get these powerful financial management tools:</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Credit and financial consulting through nonprofit organizations</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Credit score simulators that predict actions and potential consequences as your life changes</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Links to pertinent information</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n			<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Facts on the industry, including identity theft</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><font color="#343434"><span style="font-style: normal"><b>With EnCharge, you not only know your score - you understand it.</b></span></font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n', 3),
(17, 'riskmanager', 'consumers/riskmanager', 'Why is EnCharge Important', 'Cost of Membership versus Cost of Errors', '<p>\r\n	<img align="right" alt="Credit Report" height="111" src="/images/icons/credit-report.jpg" width="171" /><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 26px; ">In today&rsquo;s credit industry, any mistake on your credit report can result in higher interest rates. An error on your report can have an immediate effect and lower your score by as much as 100 points.&nbsp; If you started at 720, your score could drop as low as 620 from a simple mistake.&nbsp; That could increase your interest rate by as much as 2%, possibly more.&nbsp;&nbsp;A difference of 1% on a $100,000 loan translates to a $59.40 increase in interest per month equaling $1425.60 a year, $7128.00 for 5 years, and $21,386.27 over 30 years. At $200,000, your yearly cost would increase by $2,851.20.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Having accurate information on your credit report is absolutely critical. Would you spend $90 to save $2800?&nbsp;&nbsp;There are countless horror stories involving errors on credit reports ranging from being reported dead and unable to renew a mortgage to getting stuck with bills that aren&#39;t yours.</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">EnCharge not only protects you from the effects of errors but it guarantees full defence against identity theft with our voice print technology. The loss of time and money as well as increased stress associated with identity theft and errors are often too significant to quantify.</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">Protection from these&nbsp;troubles in today&rsquo;s world is crucial and priceless.&nbsp;&nbsp;EnCharge can help you avoid reporting errors and identity theft&nbsp;simply and permanently.</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2">An EnCharge membership is only $90 annually, but what are the real savings for you?&nbsp;</font></font></font></span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; font-weight: normal; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><br />\r\n	</span></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" color="#343434" face="Verdana, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 26px;"><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="font-style: normal"><span style="font-weight: normal">Save time, money, and headaches.&nbsp;</span></span></font></font></font><a href="[siteurl]/register/customer"><font color="#2f7bb0"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="font-style: normal"><span style="font-weight: normal">Join now.</span></span></font></font></font></a></span></font></p>\r\n', 3),
(18, 'billpaymentreminder', 'consumers/billpaymentreminder', 'Bill Payment Reminder Service', '', '<p>\r\n	<img align="right" alt="Resource Center" height="111" src="/images/icons/toolbox.jpg" width="111" /><span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18px; ">Everyone has bills and anyone can forget to make a payment on time. On average, an individual&rsquo;s credit score drops by nearly 100 points with one late payment.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18px; ">The EnCharge Bill Payment Reminder service allows members to minimize unintentional damage to their credit score by sending them a monthly email reminder. Members simply complete the payment information template and include their email address to receive a monthly email reminder up to five&nbsp;days prior to the registered payment due date.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 150%; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small; ">The Bill Payment Reminder Service is a great tool to help members stay organized and maintain their credit score. It&rsquo;s just one more reason to&nbsp;join EnCharge.</span></p>\r\n', 3),
(19, 'controlpower', 'controlpower', 'Power', 'Welcome to enCharge! We believe that Power and Control must be Paired to be Valuable.', '<p>\r\n	Power</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	EnCharge offers the power of identity security, correct lender information, verified files and complete account access. EnCharge keeps the process simple by offering members control over file access, unlimited browsing of its content and real issue resolution service managed by agents in near real time. Members call in with questions which our teams research and forward information using the fastest technologies available.&nbsp;Give us a call, email us or make online comments at your convenience. Members are part of the process of accuracy and protection. We want them fully involved in their own credit report management.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Choose Power, Choose Control, Choose to be EnCharge.</p>\r\n', NULL),
(20, 'fraudbuster', 'creditors/fraudbuster', 'Fraud Buster', '', '<p>\r\n	<img align="right" alt="Fraud Buster" height="111" src="/images/icons/fraud-buster.jpg" width="171" /> Security is of paramount concern at EnCharge. As a result, socials (SSN and SIN) will not be used for account identification, verification or any other purpose. Membership account verification with EnCharge is based on voice print biometrics, collected and managed realtime by our cutting-edge, biometric partner in conjunction with other information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	One of the many advantages of our biometric system is that multiple accounts cannot be created for any single member. By linking individual voiceprints to a file, and using this voiceprint to authorize any release of credit or to access information, consumers can be assured that no fraud will occur on their EnCharge file. A fraudster having access to all of an EnCharge members information is still unable to create, access or misuse another members file as the biometric security is in place.&nbsp; Not even digital recordings of a member will grant access as the voiceprint analytic software is capable of detecting reproductions.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	Additionally, there is no incentive for anyone to attempt to create an EnCharge credit file in the name of another as this new credit &nbsp;file will need to be built to from scratch and well managed to produce a credit score worthy of obtaining credit.&nbsp;Further, the fraudster will&nbsp;be stuck with the account for life since his or her voice print is paired to the account.&nbsp; &nbsp;Duplicate voice print pairing is only permitted in rare cases eg: power of attorney, parent/guardian account pairing and only where complete documentation is filed and verified.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	Persons attempting fraud, fail and having provided irrefutable proof of intent may be added to a list of known fraudsters or K.F.L (Known Fraudster List). Within EnCharge environments being present on the list may;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Prevent EnCharge account creation</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Reduce the likelihood of obtaining credit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Increase interest rates from lenders willing to take the risk</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Open one to prosecution</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	All new member applications will be processed against the K.F.L. biometrically prior to final approval.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<a href="/register/customer">Join EnCharge</a> to set up your account now.</p>\r\n', 5),
(21, 'howarewedifferent', 'creditors/howarewedifferent', 'How are we different?', '', '<p>\r\n	How is EnCharge Different?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our reports are 100% ERROR FREE.&nbsp; We offer a more predictive score and actionable reports that deliver real value.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Statistics show that 79% of credit reports have errors, 29% of those serious enough to result in automatic denial. Furthermore, when one pulls a file from all 3 agencies, the person will only be categorized in the same risk level 55% of the time.&nbsp; We have all heard the stories where a person goes in to renew their mortgage and to be told they cant because...&quot;they are dead&quot;... , at least according to the agencies.&nbsp; This will never happen with EnCharge, since the members voice will confirm if they are alive.&nbsp; Simple, Effective.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Here is something you may have not known.&nbsp; When you request a credit report from the 3 agencies,&nbsp; a common name can return as many as 1500, yes 1500 different files. That&#39;s with using DOB and SSN or SIN. With no way of&nbsp;knowing which file&nbsp;really belongs to whom.&nbsp; EnCharge has only one file per member voiceprint ever.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our process is one were all reports are linked to the specific file number not &ldquo;fished&rdquo; or &ldquo;mined&rdquo; into random or incomplete reports. Reports are made only by registered and biometrically authenticated companies that offer credit or services like power or water. This allows research to be complete and accurate. Our service is web based and uses web services so that implementation is seamless for individual members, member businesses and member creditors. Companies that use our service will reduce their fraudulent credit attempts and thereby operating costs. This enhances their shareholder wealth.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;<strong>Lastly, our service is FREE to Creditors. &nbsp;What do you pay for your current provider? So what are you waiting for, Be EnCharge Today.</strong></p>\r\n', 5),
(22, '100percentaccurate', 'creditors/100percentaccurate', '100% Accurate', 'Our credit Report', '<p>\r\n	Our credit file is the only 100% accurate report.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It also empowers and protects your customer. The credit report provides more than just past and current credit information, it also may include verified income, level of education and other household information that is relevant to informed financial decisions.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Target Market</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	At enCharge, we go even further, members have the ability to select products they would be interested in being solicited for such as mutual fund or credit cards, making you marketing efforts more cost effective.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Risk attributes</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The credit file also includes 2 generated scores which are explained in the next section. It can also produce a suggested interest rate if desired. The scores are risk indicative in so far as a 697 is saying the&nbsp;creditor has a 77.6% chance of getting paid back.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Without Borders</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition, because our system relies on membership numbers and biometrics, it doesn&rsquo;t use SSN or SIN to identify a report, thus our reports are global and not limited by national borders or immigration status. If a member moves from Canada to the US, their report moves with them. A member creditor gains access to the members file via the website using their membership number and biometric confirmation. Think of all the people that relocate to other countries and have to start from scratch, you can&rsquo;t lend to them, but in our system you can, provided their score warrants it.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each new member has a credit file built from scratch.&nbsp; This is to ensure the report is 100% error free, which is the basis for a file to have any real value.&nbsp; The sooner creditors use EnCharge, the sooner the full value can be realized.&nbsp; Each time a creditor reports on a member,&nbsp; the historical information is reported such as age of account, number of late payments, if any; allowing the files, even though new, to quickly have the historical depth needed to make decisions.</p>\r\n', 5),
(23, 'c-thescore', 'creditors/c-thescore', 'The Score', 'Our score', '<p>\r\n	<img align="right" alt="Credit Report" height="111" src="/images/icons/credit-report.jpg" width="171" /> EnCharge&#39;s risk algorithm produces a dual risk score designed for the realities of today and measures true financial risk.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The score ranges from 300 - 900. It first produces an all inclusive score, similar to current processes but with simpler and more predictive qualities. Secondarily, we also generate a score without bankruptcy, judgments and liens.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is to provide the creditor with a far more accurate picture and allows for better questions and assessments. The reason is, in some jurisdictions, liens are placed on a property before construction or renovations can begin or in others, divorces are forced by the courts into bankruptcy to dispose of assets and judgments are not always a bad thing. Sometimes it makes sense to go to court to settle a matter and it is a persons legal right to do so. The EnCharge process provides the information necessary so that when combined with good judgment everyone does well.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our score and report accounts for legal actions by reviewing the appropriate court filings as well as providing the two scores. If a person is not paying their bills, it will come up in the second score and you will know they are a bad risk. However, if they have a solid second score and the first gives one pause, you can quickly determined what happen, easily assess the true risk and forge a relationship accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Another unique feature of our algorithm and score is that it takes into account credit solutions that are secured by a CD in the US and GICs in Canada. It doesn&rsquo;t make sense to penalize someone&rsquo;s score because they are using 90% of the credit line if it is fully secured. It is just not a true measurement of risk and one could be forced to turn down a potential client do to outdated algorithms.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It also doesn&rsquo;t double count the same offense nor do we use the scorecard methodology.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Lastly, it measures true risk not just information. For example; If a person is in an accident and ends up in a coma, what are the chances of them paying all their bills while in a coma? In these types of events, EnCharge members, once able, could contact us to explain the situation. EnCharge will verify their story and keep the medical records on file to prove it. Once verified, EnCharge can offer modifications to their score for any negative information resulting from the appropriate time frame. Why would we do this? Because it&rsquo;s not a true measurement of risk. This is not a matter of financial mismanagement nor is it a matter of character. Since not all bill payments are pre-authorized withdrawals; no reasonable person would expect a person while in a coma to be able to pay all their bills on time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 5),
(24, 'process', 'creditors/process', 'Process', 'How do I get a members credit report?', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 16px">Creditor access to member files is simple and secure. First, visit the </span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 16px">EnCharge</span><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 16px"> website and log on by clicking on the creditors tab and entering the branch information. On this page, a creditor will be required to input his or her user number and password. Upon verification, they will have access to a credit report request page. On this page, creditors will input the members&rsquo; credit number, either manually or by swiping the membership card and entering the amount sought. Also, the creditor will be required to click a checkbox indicating if the member is with him or her before submitting the request.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-size: 16px">Once submitted,&nbsp;our system&nbsp;will immediately contact our member, either directly or through the creditor depending on which box was checked during the request. The risk management&nbsp;system will ask the member whether he or she is applying for credit and if so to provide his or her PIN which will be matched numerically and by voice print. If the member responds that they are not attempting to obtain credit or cannot provide the appropriate PIN or the biometrics do not match up, it will be deemed a fraudulent attempt. As a result, the creditor will not be able to view the report. In addition the bank will be notified of the attempt and the data stored regarding the amount sought, notice will be given to notify the authorities and the voiceprint flag for future reference. In the event the consumer member is indeed seeking credit and is able to provide the appropriate PIN, the credit file will be released to the creditor for their review.&nbsp;</span></font></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 18px; font-size: 16px">In the event of approval, a file number will be generated, which allows the creditor to supply credit information on the members credit file, but only with regards to the accounts approved at the time the request was made.</span></font></p>\r\n', 5),
(25, 'howmuch', 'creditors/howmuch', 'FREE', 'What does this cost?', '<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 16px"><strong>Its Free. &nbsp;The only cost to you is not using EnCharge. &nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="font-size: 16px"><strong>Protect you institution today. &nbsp;<a href="/register/creditor">Join EnCharge</a></strong></span></p>\r\n', 5),
(26, 'certified', 'certified', 'EnCharge Certified', 'Coming soon', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 88, 150); font-family: ''Trebuchet MS'', sans-serif; font-size: xx-large; font-weight: bold; line-height: 42px; ">Get Encharge Certified</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.92cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#005189"><font face="Trebuchet MS, sans-serif"><font size="5"><b>(this feature is coming soon!)<br />\r\n	</b></font></font></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">Get an EnCharge Certificate placed on your site! </font></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">Member Institutions can qualify for an EnCharge Certificate. &nbsp;This certificate (calculated in real time) rates credit-seeker satisfaction with your customer service. In order to qualify for the certificate, member institutions&nbsp;must achieve an 80% or higher customer satisfaction rating. &nbsp;</font></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">The certificate is issued by measuring three levels of achievement: bronze, silver or gold. Bronze runs from 80% -86%, silver from 87%-93%, and gold from 94% and higher. &nbsp;Customer satisfaction levels are calculated by using the total number of members subscribing to your service versus the number of &ldquo;UPPs&rdquo; filed against your firm. By achieving the EnCharge certificate, credit-seekers can quickly tell what level of service to expect.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">This is your company&rsquo;s chance to stand out and shine! You will be able to differentiate your firm from competitors and gauge&nbsp;how well&nbsp;your business is delivering its brand and providing customer service.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif">The EnCharge Certificate is the only immediate customer service indicator in the industry. &nbsp;You cannot buy it. It is earned and can be tracked, lost, or upgraded in real-time; just one more reason for your best-in-class company to join EnCharge today!</font></font></p>\r\n', NULL),
(27, 'i-fraudbuster', 'i-fraudbuster', 'The EnCharge ID Theft', '', '<p>\r\n	<span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(52, 52, 52); font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 26px; ">As a premier risk management firm, one of Encharge&rsquo;s biggest advantages is the &ldquo;ID Theft&rdquo; solution. Our company&rsquo;s strategic partner, Voice Vault (a leader in remote biometric security solutions), has enabled the EnCharge ID Theft to collect biometric authentications. By using voiceprint technology at each point of entry, minor data management is automated while access to individual files and reports is biometrically encoded. Therefore, registered credit-seekers, lending institutions and reporting companies are armed with the ability to access files solely via the voice portal &ndash; the ultimate way to protect information.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 0.71cm; widows: 0; orphans: 0">\r\n	<font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"><b>What does this mean for our clients?</b></font></font><font color="#343434"><font face="Verdana, sans-serif"> Imagine a reality where social security numbers are no longer used as a foundation for credit files, thus eliminating the ability for credit information to be targeted by aggressive fraudsters.&nbsp;At EnCharge, the dream of safety and security has become a reality. Since the user&rsquo;s voice is required for file access, information is fully protected from risks that are currently associated with identity&nbsp;theft. With the Fraud Buster,&nbsp;all entries to a person&rsquo;s credit file are&nbsp;authenticated, scrutinized and confirmed before taking effect. This enables EnCharge to verify the identity of the individual who is requesting a credit file and that this information is&nbsp;100% correct.&nbsp;&nbsp;Full protection and accuracy provides creditors with the best information possible so credit-seekers get the funds they need when they need them.</font></font></p>\r\n', NULL);
